llccaasseepp -- Command

Convert text to lower case
llccaasseepp [-ff _i_n_p_u_t_f_i_l_e] [-oo _o_u_t_p_u_t_f_i_l_e]

The command  llccaasseepp converts characters in its input  stream to lower case.
If  you do  not name  an _i_n_p_u_t_f_i_l_e  on the command  line, llccaasseepp  reads the
standard input.  If  you do not name an _o_u_t_p_u_t_f_i_l_e,  it writes it output to
the standard output.

_S_e_e _A_l_s_o
ccoommmmaannddss, mmaaiill

_N_o_t_e_s
The COHERENT command ssmmaaiill uses  llccaasseepp to convert headers on mail messages
to  convert  addresses  to lower  case.   Normally,  users  do  not run  it
directly.
